<TITLE> Aman, Bakir sued for tax dodge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 30 (bdnews24.com)  The National Board of Revenue Monday sued former BNP state minister Amanullah Aman and BNP leader BM Bakir Hossain on charges of tax dodging. Md Monwar Hossain Munshi, deputy commissioner of tax, NBR, filed a case against Aman at 10:30am with Dhaka Senior Judge's Court. The case details said the accused evaded paying Tk 1.52 crore in income taxes during 1992-93, 1993-94, 1997-98 and 2001-06 taxation years. NBR's assistant commissioner of tax Tasmiah Delwar filed a case against Bakir with the same court for tax evasion. The case details said Bakir dodged payment of Tk 6.6 lakh in income taxes in 2000-01 and 2006-07 taxation years. Thirteen witnesses have been listed in Aman's case statement and eight in Bakir's. bdnews
